{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Soufflé","content":["Preheat oven to 200°C.","Place dill and chilli (if using) in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Add smoked salmon, cream, egg yolks, 1 pinch of salt, pepper and nutmeg then blend <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl thoroughly."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites, cream of tartar and a pinch of salt in mixing bowl then, without measuring cup, whisk <b>1-2 min\/speed 3.5<b> until stiff peaks form. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>, transfer whisked whites to a bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl and make sauce."]},{"title":"Sauce","content":["Place leeks and oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add wine, stock and water then, without measuring cup, cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, fold whisked egg whites into reserved soufflé base using a metal spoon.","Heat oil in an oven-proof frying pan (Ø 26 cm) until sizzling, then add fresh salmon. Pour soufflé mix over salmon and bake for 15-17 minutes (200°C) until the top is lightly browned. Meanwhile, finish sauce.","Add butter and lemon juice to mixing bowl then cook <b>1 min\/100°C\/speed 3<b> then blend <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>. Add salt and pepper to taste and extra dill then transfer to a serving jug.","Serve soufflé immediately with sauce and buttered toast on the side."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Soufflé","content":["6 sprigs fresh dill, plus extra to taste","1 fresh chilli, deseeded, cut in pieces (optional)","150 g hot smoked salmon, deboned, skinless, cut in pieces","100 g single cream","4 egg yolks, from medium eggs","2 pinches fine sea salt, plus extra to taste","1 pinch ground black pepper, plus extra to taste","1 pinch ground nutmeg","4 egg whites, from medium eggs","1 pinch cream of tartar"]},{"title":"Sauce","content":["60 g leeks, white part only, sliced","20 g extra virgin olive oil","150 g white wine","½ fish stock cube (for 0.5 l)","150 g water","1 Tbsp olive oil","600 g fresh salmon fillets, skinless","100 g unsalted butter, diced","½ lemon, juice only"]}],"id":"r238743","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-qVGEja5_mGw\/XZQvL4K0euI\/AAAAAAAAca0\/ljyHKoeLChMnM4GormhpgIsXYH_LKJJ3wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_CxrMto87QVXWT3Yh.png","title":"Salmon Soufflé","publishedAt":"2017-11-20T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"11.5 g","fat":"17 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"1.5 g","calories":"882.8 kJ \/ 211 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, serving jug, oven-proof frying pan, oven","hintsAndTricks":["After placing souffle in the oven, fill a sauce boat or jug with hot water. Discard water just before pouring in the finished sauce; this will help keep the sauce warm.","The sauce can be made in advance, blended <strong>3 sec\/speed 5<\/strong>, then reheated <strong>3 min\/80°C\/speed <\/strong> just before serving.","This dish can be made for 2 people using the same quantity of souffle but only 2 pieces of salmon.","The sauce may be served with any simple fish dish."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h","4 portions"]}